
[1]aceldama

   ACEL'DAMA, n.

   A field said to have laid south of Jerusalem, the same as the potters
   field, purchased with the bribe which Judas took for betraying his
   master, and therefore called the field of blood. It was appropriated to
   the interment of strangers.
